cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with interpreting and correcting predictions made by a DNN object detector. It also involves image processing and feature importance values. The paper also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a practical approach to interpret decisions made by a DNN object detector. Additionally, it involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with deep neural networks. The paper also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as it proposes a software tool that can be used for cluster processing. Lastly, it involves cryptography and security (cs.CR) as it proposes a potential extension of the E2X framework to overcome failures after model retraining.
